Reasoning: 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is likely because the paper discusses the implementation of peridynamics using a specific software library (HPX) and presents convergence results. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is likely because the paper discusses the use of asynchronous many task systems on modern supercomputers to address the computational resources required for peridynamics. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is likely because the paper discusses the numerical methods used for time integration and presents convergence results. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is possible because the paper discusses the design of the code for modular expandability. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is possible because the paper discusses the application of peridynamics to fracture mechanics.
